'''Sanbu Ubayama Shell Midden''' (山武姥山貝塚) is a [[shell midden]] dating from the [[Jōmon period]], located in {{ill|Yokoshibahikari|ja|横芝光町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokoshibahikari|qq=}}, {{ill|Sanbu District, Chiba|ja|山武郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanbu District, Chiba|qq=}}, [[Chiba Prefecture]]. It serves as a type site for Ubayama-style pottery (Ubayama I, II, III, IV styles) from the late Jōmon period. To distinguish it from the similarly named Ubayama Shell Midden in {{ill|Ichikawa, Chiba|ja|市川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikawa, Chiba|qq=}}, this site is referred to as the "Sanbu Ubayama Shell Midden."<ref>[https://www.town.yokoshibahikari.chiba.jp/soshiki/14/1395.html#a08 Jōmon Period Sites], Yokoshibahikari Town Official Website.</ref>

{{coord|35|40|08.4|N|140|26|39.9|E|region:JP-12|display=title}}{{Location map|Japan Chiba|lat_deg=35|lat_min=40|lat_sec=08.4|lon_deg=140|lon_min=26|lon_sec=39.9|label=Sanbu Ubayama<br>Shell Midden|position=bottom|mark=Red pog.svg|marksize=10|width=200|caption={{center|}}}}

== Overview ==  
The shell midden is situated on a plateau, forming a semi-horseshoe shape with eight clusters of shell layers facing valley heads. This configuration represents a transitional form between point-ring and ring shell middens. The site is estimated to have been inhabited from approximately 5,000 years ago during the middle Jōmon period until around 2,500 years ago in the late Jōmon period.  

The midden primarily consists of brackish and freshwater shell species such as [[Chosenshima hamaguri]], [[Danbei kisago]], [[Yamato shijimi]], [[Uminina]], [[Bai]], and [[Shiofuki]].<ref>{{cite book|author=Yokoshibahikari Town Board of Education|url=https://sitereports.nabunken.go.jp/ja/70311|title=Sanbu Ubayama Shell Midden: Exhibition Catalog and 2019 Excavation Report|publisher=Yokoshibahikari Town Board of Education|year=2020|doi=10.24484/sitereports.70311|CRID=1130575020489308942}}</ref>  

Since 1956, six excavations have been conducted, uncovering numerous artifacts.<ref>[https://maruchiba.jp/spot/detail_10243.html Sanbu Ubayama Shell Midden - Chiba Tourism Navi], Chiba Prefecture Official Tourism Site.</ref>

== Surrounding Area ==  
