'''Sanbu Ubayama Shell Midden''' (山武姥山貝塚) is a [[shell midden]] dating from the [[Jōmon period]], located in [[:en:Yokoshibahikari|Yokoshibahikari]], [[:en:Sanbu District|Sanbu District, Chiba]], [[:en:Chiba Prefecture|Chiba Prefecture]]. It serves as a type site for Ubayama-style pottery (Ubayama I, II, III, IV styles) from the late Jōmon period. To distinguish it from the similarly named Ubayama Shell Midden in [[:en:Ichikawa, Chiba|Ichikawa, Chiba]], this site is referred to as the "Sanbu Ubayama Shell Midden."<ref>[https://www.town.yokoshibahikari.chiba.jp/soshiki/14/1395.html#a08 Jōmon Period Sites], Yokoshibahikari Town Official Website.</ref>

{{coord|35|40|08.4|N|140|26|39.9|E|region:JP-12|display=title}}{{Location map|Japan Chiba|lat_deg=35|lat_min=40|lat_sec=08.4|lon_deg=140|lon_min=26|lon_sec=39.9|label=Sanbu Ubayama<br>Shell Midden|position=bottom|mark=Red pog.svg|marksize=10|width=200|caption={{center|}}}}

== Overview ==  
The shell midden is situated on a plateau, forming a semi-horseshoe shape with eight clusters of shell layers facing valley heads. This configuration represents a transitional form between point-ring and ring shell middens. The site is estimated to have been inhabited from approximately 5,000 years ago during the middle Jōmon period until around 2,500 years ago in the late Jōmon period.  

The midden primarily consists of brackish and freshwater shell species such as [[Chosenshima hamaguri]], [[Danbei kisago]], [[Yamato shijimi]], [[Uminina]], [[:en:Bai|Bai]], and [[Shiofuki]].<ref>{{cite book|author=Yokoshibahikari Town Board of Education|url=https://sitereports.nabunken.go.jp/ja/70311|title=Sanbu Ubayama Shell Midden: Exhibition Catalog and 2019 Excavation Report|publisher=Yokoshibahikari Town Board of Education|year=2020|doi=10.24484/sitereports.70311|CRID=1130575020489308942}}</ref>  

Since 1956, six excavations have been conducted, uncovering numerous artifacts.<ref>[https://maruchiba.jp/spot/detail_10243.html Sanbu Ubayama Shell Midden - Chiba Tourism Navi], Chiba Prefecture Official Tourism Site.</ref>

== Surrounding Area ==  
The area surrounding the midden is rich in archaeological sites, including the Nakadai Shell Midden, Konosu Shell Midden, Kidoba Shell Midden, and Ushikuma Shell Midden. To the east lies the [[:en:Kuriyama River|Kuriyama River]], known for numerous discoveries of Jōmon-period [[:en:Dugout canoe|dugout canoes]], especially in upstream areas such as [[:en:Tako, Chiba|Tako]] and [[:en:Sōsa|Sōsa]]. To the south lies the Sakata Lagoon, believed to be a former lagoon during the Jōmon period. To the north is the [[:en:Shibayama Kofun Cluster|Shibayama Kofun Cluster]], famous for expressive human-shaped {{ill|haniwa|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/haniwa|qq=}} figurines.  

